# Technical Design Document: High-Scale Lead Discovery Engine

## 1. Executive Summary

**Objective:** Provide a real-time, sortable search interface for 50M leads across 20+ normalized tables.
**Core Challenge:** Sub-3s latency for "recently updated" sorts and dynamic filtering without using database triggers.
**Proposed Solution:** An event-driven **Summary Table** acting as a Read Model, indexed with **GIN** for dynamic JSONB attributes, and exposed via an **MCP-powered LLM layer**.

---

## 2. System Architecture

### 2.1 Component Context

The system moves from a "Pull" architecture (expensive joins) to a "Push" architecture (event-driven projection).

```mermaid
graph TD
    subgraph "Producer Services"
        S1[Lead Service]
        S2[Activity Service]
        S20[Notes Service]
    end

    subgraph "Event Bus"
        K[(Kafka Cluster)]
    end

    subgraph "Read Model Layer"
        W[Projection Worker]
        DB[(PostgreSQL 16+)]
        ST[lead_search_summary]
    end

    S1 -- Emit Change --> K
    S2 -- Emit Change --> K
    S20 -- Emit Change --> K
    K -- Consume --> W
    W -- Atomic Upsert --> ST

```

