## 3. Data Ingestion & Projection

### 3.1 Sequence Diagram: Event-Driven Projection

This flow ensures that any change in the 20+ source tables is reflected in the search index with minimal lag.

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant S as Source Service
    participant K as Kafka Topic
    participant W as Projection Worker
    participant DB as Summary Table

    Note over S, DB: Change occurs in one of 20+ source tables
    S->>K: Publish Event {lead_id: 123, update: {...}}
    K->>W: Fetch Event
    W->>W: Map Update to JSONB Schema
    W->>DB: UPSERT (id, last_activity_at, filter_attributes)
    Note over DB: GREATEST(current_ts, event_ts)
    DB-->>W: Acknowledge

```

### 3.2 SQL Schema & Indexing Strategy

```sql
CREATE TABLE lead_search_summary (
    lead_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    last_activity_at TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE NOT NULL,
    status VARCHAR(50),
    -- High-speed filtering blob
    filter_attributes JSONB NOT NULL DEFAULT '{}',
    -- Data for UI rendering (reduces back-joins)
    display_metadata JSONB NOT NULL DEFAULT '{}'
);

-- Index for the primary 'Recent' sort
CREATE INDEX idx_leads_activity_sort ON lead_search_summary (last_activity_at DESC);

-- Index for dynamic filtering across the JSONB blob
CREATE INDEX idx_leads_gin_filters ON lead_search_summary 
USING GIN (filter_attributes jsonb_path_ops);

```

