## 4. Natural Language Search Layer (LLM + MCP)

The user interacts with the data via natural language. The LLM acts as a semantic translator, using the **Model Context Protocol (MCP)** to communicate with the database tools safely.

### 4.1 Sequence Diagram: Natural Language Query Flow

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant U as User (UI)
    participant L as LLM (Brain)
    participant M as MCP Server (Tools)
    participant G as GraphQL / DB
    participant ST as Summary Table

    U->>L: "Find tech leads in Austin over 90 score"
    L->>M: List available tools?
    M-->>L: search_leads(industry, city, min_score)
    L->>M: Call search_leads(industry='Tech', city='Austin', min_score=90)
    M->>G: Execute Query (JSONB Containment)
    G->>ST: SELECT * FROM summary WHERE ...
    ST-->>G: 1,200 Rows
    G-->>M: Result Data
    M-->>L: Raw Results (JSON)
    L-->>U: "I found 1,200 tech leads in Austin..."

```

